	that allows the time-varying spatial weight distribution of the active
	office environment to be captured. The properties of the active floor
	are described, showing that it differs substantially from other commonly
	encountered sensor systems. Furthermore, classification of the footstep
	signature of a number of individuals is attempted by application
	of the hidden Markov model technique},
