  abstract = {Smart homes integrated with sensors, actuators, wireless networks
	and context-aware middleware soon becomes part of our daily life.
	This paper describes a context-aware middleware providing an automatic
	home service based on a user's preference inside a smart home. The
	context-aware middleware includes an appliance controller, a context-aware
	agent and a scalable browser. The appliance controller takes charge
	of communication between appliances in the context-aware middleware.
	The context-aware middleware use OSGi (open service gateway initial)
	as the framework of the home network. The scalable browser recognizes
	the properties of all the rendering device, and it figures out their
	screen size. We use UlML (user interface markup language) as multiple
	rendering device. The context-aware agent utilizes 6 basic data values
	for learning and predicting the user's preference for the home appliances:
	the pulse, the body temperature, the facial expression, the room
	temperature, the time, and the location. The six data sets construct
	the context model and are used by the context manager module. The
	user profile manager maintains the history information for home appliances
	chosen by the user. The user-pattern learning and predicting module
	is based on a neural network, which predicts the proper home service
	for the user. The test results show that the pattern of an individual's
	preference can be effectively evaluated.},
