  monthfiled = {February},
  abstract = {A temperature control system utilizes detected occupancy and activity
	levels to automatically condition a response of an HVAC system to
	a difference between a setpoint temperature and an actual temperature
	within a zone. The illustrated example includes an infrared sensor
	that provides at least one signal indicating the activity and occupancy
	levels in the zone. A neural network processes the sensor signal
	to provide an indication of the occupancy and activity levels to
	a controller. The controller automatically adjusts at least one control
	parameter of the HVAC system to compensate for changes in the occupancy
	or activity levels that would affect the temperature comfort setting
	in the zone},
