	, metron = measure ) is the field of study that involves methods
	of unique recognition of humans based on one or many intrinsic physical
	or/and behavioral characteristics. In ICT, biometric authentication
	refers to technologies that analyze and measure human physical and
	behavioral features for the purpose of authentication. Identification
	of a person involves extracting of biometric info from a person and
	then comparing this info with samples stored in database. Identification
	is more far more complex than verification as the biometric information
	has to be compared with all other entries in the database in order
	to provide a definite answer.},
