  month = {May},
  abstract = {We propose an intelligent agent model for smart home environments.
	In ubiquitous computing environments like smart home, agents have
	to learn user's preferences in order to assist them. These preferences
	are represented by user profiles. Our proposed UT-AGENT uses case-based
	reasoning (CBR) to acquire knowledge about user actions that are
	worth recording to determine their preferences and Bayesian network
	(BN) as an inference tool to model relationships between them. UT-AGENT
	maintains the status of every device present in the home and activates
	them as per user preference. It generates a sequence of expected
	user's query and simultaneously activates the devices with preset
	preference settings.},
