	in-building and short-range wireless communication. Many mobile devices
	such as mobile robots, laptops and PDAs already use this protocol
	for wireless communication. Many wireless Ethernet cards measure
	the signal strength of incoming packets. This paper investigates
	the feasibility of implementing a localization system using this
	sensor. Using a Bayesian localization framework, we show experiments
	demonstrating that off-the-shelf wireless hardware can accurately
	be used for location sensing and tracking with about one meter precision
	in a wireless-enabled office building.},
