	over 900 sensor inputs, including wired reed switches, current and
	water flow inputs, object and person motion detectors, and RFID tags.
	Our aim was to compare different sensor modalities on data that approached
	"real world" conditions, where the subject and annotator were unaffiliated
	with the authors. We found that 10 infra-red motion detectors outperformed
