  abstract = {Visualization has been successfully applied to analyse time-dependent
	data for a long time now. Lately, a number of new approaches have
	been introduced, promising more effective graphs especially for large
	datasets and multi-parameter data. In this paper, we give an overview
	on the visualization of time-series data and the available techniques.
	We provide a taxonomy and discuss general aspects of time-dependent
	data. After an overview on conventional techniques we discuss techniques
	for analysing time-dependent multivariate data sets in more detail.
	After this, we give an overview on dynamic presentation techniques
	and event-based visualization.},
