	of over 200 motion sensors connected in a wireless network observing
	a medium-sized office space populated with almost 100 people for
	a period of almost a year. We use a tracklet graph representation
	of the data in the sensor network, which allows us to efficiently
	evaluate gross patterns of office-wide social behavior of its occupants
