	social events that affect the entire population of the space. We
	present our experiments with a method based on Kullback-Leibler metric
	applied to the office activity modelled as a Markov process. Using
	this approach we detect gross deviations of short term office-wide
	behavior patterns from previous long-term patterns spanning various
	time intervals. We compare detected deviations to the company calendar
